--- title: Fastseq Alt readme keywords: fastai sidebar: home_sidebar summary: "A way to use fastai with sequence data" ---

Installing¶

Please install fastai2 according to the instructions.

Then install Fastseq by:

pip install -e .

How to use¶

from fastseq.all import *
from fastai2.basics import *
from fastseq.models.nbeats import *
from fastseq.data.external import *

items = dummy_data_generator(50, 15, nrows=1000)
data = TSDataBunch.from_items(items, horizon = 7, lookback=30, step=3)
data.show_batch()

Train:3000; Valid: 3000; Test 1000

# TODO make custom learner with custom model
learn = nbeats_learner(data,layers=[1024, 1024], stack_types=("trend","seasonality"), b_loss=.1,nb_blocks_per_stack=10,
                       loss_func= CombinedLoss(F.mse_loss, smape, ratio = {'smape':.1})
                      )

from fastai2.callback.all import *
learn.lr_find()

learn.fit_one_cycle(2, 1e-4)
learn.recorder.plot_loss()
epoch train_loss valid_loss mae smape mse_loss theta b_loss time
0 4.268614 2.939240 0.442330 0.681342 0.390768 11.676650 406.937286 00:07
1 3.148998 2.170563 0.480000 0.729369 0.442526 13.808448 269.131683 00:07 
learn.show_results(1,max_n=9)

Interperation¶

from fastai2.interpret import *
from fastseq.interpret import *

interp = NBeatsInterpretation.from_learner(learn)

interp.plot_top_losses(3)
